data.enText: to bring sb/sth under control, especially by using force

data.chText: 军队被调来镇压反叛者。
data.enText: Troops were called in to subdue the rebels.
to calm or control your feelings

data.chText: 朱莉娅不得不克制住自己，不去抚摩他的头发。
data.enText: Julia had to subdue an urge to stroke his hair.

simple_means.memory_skill: sub 下 + due〔 = duc引导〕→ 引到下面 → 征服

tr: to put down by force or authority

example: Our wishes have to be subordinated to that of our ruler

tr: put down by force or intimidation
example: The government quashes any attempt of an uprising
China keeps down her dissidents very efficiently
The rich landowners subjugated the peasants working the land

value.def: If soldiers or the police subdue a group of people, they defeat them or bring them under control by using force.

example.ex: Senior government officials admit they have not been able to subdue the rebels.
example.tran: 政府高级官员承认他们还没能制服反叛者。

value.def: To subdue feelings means to make them less strong.

example.ex: He forced himself to subdue and overcome his fears.
example.tran: 他强迫自己克制并战胜恐惧心理。
